18/08/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- The cabinet is preparing a set of tax relief measures to take effect next year, Finance Minister George Alogoskoufis said on Thursday (17 August). 
He explained that this would be the final phase of tax reform launched in 2004, and overall, would grant relief of up to 150m euros. 
Alogoskoufis stressed that the tax policy has yielded positive results, boosting economic growth and stimulating employment. 
(ANA - 17/08/06)
